cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing and recognition. The use of wavelet and DCT features also suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as these techniques are commonly used in feature extraction for information retrieval tasks. The use of PCA for dimensionality reduction suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of a multispectral palmprint database suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of biometric-based identification suggests that it could belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
